In this task, I understood the importance of professional communication, especially through emails and social media.
A common situation where poor digital communication can cause problems is when a student sends an email to a professor without a proper subject line. 
This can create a bad impression and may even lead to the message being ignored or misunderstood.
For example, sending a message like “Send me the details” without any greeting or context can sound rude or unclear. 
Instead, using a proper subject line, greeting, and polite tone makes the message more respectful and effective.
Through this task, I learned that clear structure, polite language, and proper formatting are very important in professional communication. 
Even small details can make a big difference in how the message is received
